places.name: Aeroporto di The Valley-Wallblake
places.perex: L'Aeroporto di Anguilla, noto anche come Aeroporto Clayton J. Lloyd e già Aeroporto Wallblake, è un aeroporto britannico situato a circa 1…

places.name: Prickly Pear Cays
places.perex: Le Prickly Pear Cays, conosciute anche come Prickley Pear Cays, sono due piccole isole disabitate situate circa sei miglia a nord di Road…

places.name: Scrub Island
places.perex: Scrub Island è un'isola disabitata situata vicino alla punta orientale di Anguilla, la sua superficie è di circa 8 km².

places.name: Wallblake House
places.perex: Wallblake House is a heritage plantation house and museum annex in The Valley, Anguilla in the northeastern Caribbean.

places.name: Sandy Island
places.perex: Tiny island with quite unique atmosphere. Scuba divers will love it here - the underwater life is amazing.

places.name: Shoal Bay
places.perex: Laid-back beach with heavenly atmosphere and breathtaking sunsets. The most beautiful beach on the island.

places.name: Rendezvous Bay
places.perex: One of the most popular beaches in Anguilla. Dream-like, vast place with translucent water and mild waves.

places.name: Island Harbour
places.perex: Laid-back fishing village surrounded by cliffs. A nice getaway from the resorts and tourist crowds.

places.name: Sombrero
places.perex: Sombrero, conosciuta anche come Hat Island, è un'isola appartenente ad Anguilla, è anche una delle isole più settentrionali dell'arcipelago…

places.name: Temenos Golf Club
places.perex: This is a real gem among the Caribbean courses. 18 holes set in an intricate design make for a challenging game.

places.name: Straw Hat
places.perex: Perfect setting and imaginative fusion of international and Caribbean cuisine are what make this restaurant so popular.

places.name: The Course at Cuisinart Golf Resort & Spa
Dune Preserve Beach Bar
places.perex: This open-air club belongs to the most legendary party spots on the island. Funky place with amazing atmosphere, busy well into the night.

places.name: Blanchard's Beach Shack
places.perex: Rather pricey but totally worth it - an amazing dining experience. Top-notch menu and great selection of wines to go with it.

places.name: Koal Keel
places.perex: Beautifully restored plantation house now serves as a hub of haute cuisine. Have at least a snack here!

places.name: Spa Rituals at Cap Juluca
places.perex: This spa establishment offers a variety of Balinese and Thai treatments. Some of their services are even designed for two.

places.name: The Spa at Viceroy
places.perex: This luxurious day spa facility offers a balanced treatments addressing both your body and mind.

places.name: Malakh Day Spa
places.perex: Have a body-soothing massage right on the beach! Perfectly trained and very friendly staff.

places.name: Picante
places.perex: This restaurant is always busy, with very lively and cheerful atmosphere. Amazing sample of Caribbean cuisine.

places.name: Da'Vida
places.perex: This spot is just made for a celebration or other special opportunity. Great ambiance and top-notch food.

places.name: Barrel Stay
places.perex: Not sure whether this restaurant is so much loved for its stupendous food or spectacular location.

places.name: Heritage Collection Museum
places.perex: This unpretentious museum is where you can learn many interesting facts about the history of Anguilla.

places.name: Anguilla Tennis Center
places.perex: Those who like active recreation should pay visit to this academy. Reasonably prices, with everything for rent.

places.name: The Pumphouse
places.perex: Restaurant, bar and cultural venue with live music almost every night. One of the most vibrant night spots on the island.

places.name: Hydroponic Farm and Organic Gardens
places.perex: This garden operates on an innovative solution of water recirculation. Very interesting technological feat as well as natural wonder.

places.name: Cheddies Carving Studio
places.perex: Interested in the local art? Stop by at this atelier owned by a local woodcarver - his work is amazing.

places.name: Devonish Art Gallery
places.perex: If you're eager to see the contemporary art created in Anguilla, search no further. A nice gallery with friendly owners.

places.name: Little Bay
places.perex: This is what you can call secluded: a charming tiny bay accessible only by boat. Unspoilt nature and crystal clear sea.

places.name: Savannah Gallery
places.perex: Whether you feel like purchasing some interesting art or not, don't miss out this gallery - it showcases amazing works.

places.name: Lynne Bernbaum Art Studio
places.perex: A working space and exhibition gallery run by an American artist. Intriguing works inspired by Anguilla nature.

places.name: Veya Restaurant
places.perex: Unpretentious, friendly, providing an amazing gourmet experience. Caribbean cuisine at its best.

places.name: Dolce Vita
places.perex: Italian restaurant that avoids the never-ending combination of pizza and pasta. Come here for perfect fish and seafood!

places.name: Hibernia
places.perex: Have a delicious meal in an awe-inspiring settings, right among the art created by the local artists.

places.name: Uncle Ernie's
places.perex: A laid-back beach bar and restaurant where you're served average meals but perfect drinks. Worth visiting for the atmosphere, too.

places.name: Meads Bay
places.perex: More than mile long, but seems like never-ending. This beach has a special charm, you'll really enjoy the ocean here.

places.name: SandBar
places.perex: Having a cocktail here and watching the sunset is an amazing experience. A large selection of tapas goes with it.

places.name: Seal Island Reef System
places.perex: This dive site is famous for an  exceptional visibility that provides good photography opportunities.

places.name: Pelican Trail
places.perex: This small park offers several water-related activities, trampoline and restaurant. Good for spending a free afternoon.

places.name: Barnes Bay
places.perex: A snorkeling paradise - there are three small reefs with vibrant life. Beautiful sandy beach that never gets crowded.

places.name: Road Bay
places.perex: This beach and marina attracts mainly the water sport lovers. Unpretentious atmosphere and great scenery.

places.name: Limestone Bay
places.perex: This natural beach is a hidden gem. A secluded stretch of fine sand and shallow entry to the sea.

places.name: Big Springs
places.perex: On this beach, you can see excavations of archaeological finds in process. There are various stone carvings, too.

places.name: Dog Island
places.perex: Privately owned island with pristine nature and several smashing beaches and scuba diving spots. A must see.

places.name: Venus Spa
places.perex: Three storeys of sheer relaxation and pleasure. Good variety of treatments inspired by the Mediterranean tradition.

places.name: Scilly Cay
places.perex: This tiny islet holds a humble restaurant and a bar. The adventurous boat trip to reach it is well worth it.

places.name: The Old Valley
places.perex: Wander around and explore the last remaining colonial houses in the island's capital.

places.name: Maundays Bay
places.perex: This beach is surrounded with stately villas and shady groves. Beautiful crescent of fine white sand that never gets crowded.

places.name: Junk’s Hole
places.perex: Rather funky bar situated on a beautiful stretch of white sand. Perfect place to snorkel and have a couple of beers afterwards.

places.name: Sandy Ground
places.perex: This is where many boat races take place. Also, it is one of the busiest beaches on the island - lots of open-air joints and sports…

places.name: Allan and Sue's Prickly Pear Restaurant
Barrel Stay Restaurant on the Beach
Atlantic Star Center of Medical Excellence
